---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Terms of Service — eKosha"
  description="Read the terms and conditions governing your use of eKosha."
>
  <Nav />
  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-24">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-4">Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="text-brand-muted mb-10">Last updated: May 2025</p>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-brand-navy mb-3">Acceptance</h2>
      <p class="text-brand-text leading-relaxed">
        By downloading or using eKosha, you agree to these Terms of Service. If you do not
        agree to these terms, please do not use the service. We may update these terms from
        time to time; continued use of the service after changes constitutes acceptance.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-brand-navy mb-3">Your Data</h2>
      <p class="text-brand-text leading-relaxed">
        You retain full ownership of all data you store in eKosha. We do not claim any
        intellectual property rights over your content. You are responsible for maintaining
        accurate records and for any sharing permissions you grant to family members or
        nominees. You may export or delete your data at any time.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-brand-navy mb-3">Acceptable Use</h2>
      <p class="text-brand-text leading-relaxed">
        You may not use eKosha for unlawful purposes, to store content that violates
        applicable Indian law, or to attempt to circumvent our encryption or access controls.
        You may not use the service to store or transmit malicious software, or to impersonate
        another person or entity.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-brand-navy mb-3">Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p class="text-brand-text leading-relaxed">
        eKosha is provided "as is" without warranties of any kind. To the maximum extent
        permitted by applicable law, we are not liable for any indirect, incidental, special,
        or consequential damages arising from your use of the service. Our aggregate liability
        to you is limited to the subscription fees paid in the three months preceding the
        event giving rise to the claim.
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
